                "href": "/profile/Pham-Gia-Hiep"
            },
            "answer_text": "If you are about French people, then Yes \u2014 there are people all around the world living in Vietnam. If you mean those specifically from the colonial time \u2014 No! The French colonial regime didn't terminate in peace, so it wasn't a good idea for French people and their families to stay in Vietnam right after the war. About French language, although Vietnam is a member of the Francophone, it is symbolic only. You cannot see a better position of French in daily life than German for example (a country with no historic relationship with Vietnam). However these days, Vietnamese still hold a positive view on France and French language and culture. ",
