                "name": "Richard Seeto",
                "href": "/profile/Richard-Seeto-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "I have visited Vietnam three times and been to such cities as Saigon (HCMC), Hanoi, Vungtau; Hue and  Da Nang. Those cities north of Saigon are more livable in terms of climate and weather. No where have I seen nor heard French being used in these places and the only vestiges of French involvement are a very few Cathedrals in Saigon and Hanoi and a museum in Hue. I have asked why so few people know the French language but the answer was that they were not taught and that it is not the lingua franca in the country. A couple of shops displayed French Names; that is all. I believe it was the French which helped codify the Vietnamese language. ",
