                "href": "/profile/Gilbert-Duy-Doan"
            },
            "answer_text": "I don\u2019t know the national statistics for second language speakers of French who live in Vietnam. The French of course have influenced Vietnamese culture through the occupation and colonization, though considerably less in chronological influence as the Chinese. The French did mandate a good writing system for translatability with western languages also written from the Latin alphabet. This makes the sound-letter or pronunciation and formal writing much easier to comprehend, and obviates a great learning curve in the language as it is represented in writing. We do have foreign languages as required and influencing Vietnamese culture in the present. You can visit a page on education written in Vietnamese on Wikipedia here, Trung h\u1ecdc c\u01a1 s\u1edf (Vi\u1ec7t Nam) \u2013 Wikipedia ti\u1ebfng Vi\u1ec7t. This cites their equivalent to middle school or lower high school, and the foreign languages they will represent in their curriculum for citizenry and affairs around the world. ",
